[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":630},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F10\u002Fvue-props-and-emit-data-passing\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F10\u002Fvue-props-and-emit-data-passing\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F10\u002Fvue-props-and-emit-data-passing\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F10\u002Fvue-props-and-emit-data-passing\u002F":606,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F10\u002Fvue-props-and-emit-data-passing\u002F":615},"\u002Fvue\u002F20190510\u002F1766915506\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":589,"date":590,"description":591,"extension":592,"lang":593,"meta":594,"navigation":595,"path":596,"readingMinutes":597,"seo":598,"standalone":599,"stem":600,"tags":601,"tldr":603,"updated":590,"url":604,"__hash__":605},"content\u002Fen\u002FVue\u002Fvue-props-and-emit-data-passing.md","How props and emit Pass Data Between Vue Components","7515961660",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":583},"minimark",[11,16,29,32,34,41,48,51,56,59,80,91,96,108,113,119,155,158,193,217,222,228,233,239,245,257,262,272,277,279,296,301,316,416,421,431,455,460,466,471,486,511,518,523,526,546,549,554,557,562,566,574,579],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19,20,24,25,28],"p",{},"I've been picking up Vue again to build something small, and since I'm splitting things into components, I need to understand how ",[21,22,23],"code",{},"props"," and ",[21,26,27],{},"emit"," pass data between them.",[17,30,31],{},"All examples below use Vue CLI 3.",[12,33,23],{"id":23},[17,35,36,37,40],{},"After scaffolding a Vue CLI 3 project, open up ",[21,38,39],{},"src\u002Fviews\u002FHome.vue",".",[17,42,43],{},[44,45],"img",{"alt":46,"src":47},"Screenshot","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FVFKOnTv.png",[17,49,50],{},"Around line 4 of the code:",[17,52,53],{},[44,54],{"alt":46,"src":55},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F68blNtc.png",[17,57,58],{},"The default scaffold already has a props example you can study.",[17,60,61,62,65,66,69,70,72,73,76,77,40],{},"Text-walking through it: ",[21,63,64],{},"Home.vue"," imports the ",[21,67,68],{},"HelloWorld"," component, then on the ",[21,71,68],{}," tag it adds a ",[21,74,75],{},"msg"," attribute and passes in ",[21,78,79],{},"Welcome to Your Vue.js App",[17,81,82,83,85,86,90],{},"This is ",[21,84,23],{}," passing data ",[87,88,89],"strong",{},"inward"," (into the component). Visualized, it looks like this:",[17,92,93],{},[44,94],{"alt":46,"src":95},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FJQ0Y4xp.png",[17,97,98,99,101,102,104,105,107],{},"Once the data lands inside the ",[21,100,68],{}," component, you need a way to receive that ",[21,103,75],{},". That's what ",[21,106,23],{}," is for. Here's the default example:",[17,109,110],{},[44,111],{"alt":46,"src":112},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FLHfN7d5.png",[17,114,115,116,118],{},"A common ",[21,117,23],{}," declaration looks like this:",[120,121,126],"pre",{"className":122,"code":123,"language":124,"meta":125,"style":125},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","props: {\n    msg: String,\n},\n","js","",[21,127,128,140,149],{"__ignoreMap":125},[129,130,133,136],"span",{"class":131,"line":132},"line",1,[129,134,23],{"class":135},"s_sBn",[129,137,139],{"class":138},"sMAXC",": {\n",[129,141,143,146],{"class":131,"line":142},2,[129,144,145],{"class":135},"    msg",[129,147,148],{"class":138},": String,\n",[129,150,152],{"class":131,"line":151},3,[129,153,154],{"class":138},"},\n",[17,156,157],{},"There's another way to write it too:",[120,159,161],{"className":122,"code":160,"language":124,"meta":125,"style":125},"props: {\n    msg: {\n      type: String,\n  },\n},\n",[21,162,163,169,175,182,188],{"__ignoreMap":125},[129,164,165,167],{"class":131,"line":132},[129,166,23],{"class":135},[129,168,139],{"class":138},[129,170,171,173],{"class":131,"line":142},[129,172,145],{"class":135},[129,174,139],{"class":138},[129,176,177,180],{"class":131,"line":151},[129,178,179],{"class":135},"      type",[129,181,148],{"class":138},[129,183,185],{"class":131,"line":184},4,[129,186,187],{"class":138},"  },\n",[129,189,191],{"class":131,"line":190},5,[129,192,154],{"class":138},[17,194,195,196,199,200,202,203,205,206,209,210,212,213,216],{},"The ",[21,197,198],{},"type"," ensures the value coming in matches the expected type. What if I change ",[21,201,75],{}," in ",[21,204,68],{}," to ",[21,207,208],{},"Number","? (Note: I haven't changed the value passed in from ",[21,211,39],{}," — it's still ",[21,214,215],{},"msg=Welcome to Your Vue.js App",".)",[17,218,219],{},[44,220],{"alt":46,"src":221},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FMVod6cP.png",[17,223,224,225,227],{},"You'll see the page renders fine — am I tricking you into thinking ",[21,226,198],{}," doesn't matter? Wrong. Open F12 > console and you'll find a red error waiting (I'm using Firefox 66 here):",[17,229,230],{},[44,231],{"alt":46,"src":232},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FQKChZti.png",[17,234,235,236,238],{},"Roughly, the red text says: \"What you passed isn't a number, it's a string — and the bad value is ",[21,237,79],{},"\".",[17,240,241,242,244],{},"So adding ",[21,243,198],{}," to props has real value — it catches bad data.",[17,246,247,248,250,251,205,254,40],{},"One more thing to watch out for: if the component doesn't declare a matching prop name, the value just gets dropped. For example, go back to ",[21,249,39],{}," and change ",[21,252,253],{},"msg=\"Welcome to Your Vue.js App\"",[21,255,256],{},"hello=\"Welcome to Your Vue.js App\"",[17,258,259],{},[44,260],{"alt":46,"src":261},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FKZU6q1E.png",[17,263,264,265,267,268,271],{},"You'll see ",[21,266,79],{}," doesn't show up on the page, and the console doesn't even warn you (and yes, I already changed the type back to ",[21,269,270],{},"String"," here).",[17,273,274],{},[44,275],{"alt":46,"src":276},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FzFRaU4p.png",[12,278,27],{"id":27},[17,280,281,283,284,286,287,289,290,286,292,295],{},[21,282,27],{}," tends to confuse people. ",[21,285,23],{}," passes data ",[87,288,89],{}," (into the component) — ",[21,291,27],{},[87,293,294],{},"outward"," (out of the component). Visualized:",[17,297,298],{},[44,299],{"alt":46,"src":300},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F0xWgeXS.png",[17,302,303,304,307,308,311,312,315],{},"So how do you use ",[21,305,306],{},"$emit"," to send data back to ",[21,309,310],{},"HOME","? First, go to ",[21,313,314],{},"src\u002Fcomponents\u002FHello.vue"," and adjust the data:",[120,317,319],{"className":122,"code":318,"language":124,"meta":125,"style":125},"export default {\n  name: 'HelloWorld',\n  props: {\n    msg: String,\n  },\n  data() {\n    return {\n      exampleMsg: 'Hello emit!',\n    }\n  },\n};\n",[21,320,321,333,345,350,355,362,375,383,394,400,407],{"__ignoreMap":125},[129,322,323,327,330],{"class":131,"line":132},[129,324,326],{"class":325},"sWyjQ","export",[129,328,329],{"class":325}," default",[129,331,332],{"class":135}," {\n",[129,334,335,338,342],{"class":131,"line":142},[129,336,337],{"class":138},"  name: ",[129,339,341],{"class":340},"sTRMh","'HelloWorld'",[129,343,344],{"class":135},",\n",[129,346,347],{"class":131,"line":151},[129,348,349],{"class":138},"  props: {\n",[129,351,352],{"class":131,"line":184},[129,353,354],{"class":138},"    msg: String,\n",[129,356,357,360],{"class":131,"line":190},[129,358,359],{"class":138},"  }",[129,361,344],{"class":135},[129,363,365,369,372],{"class":131,"line":364},6,[129,366,368],{"class":367},"sj_SG","  data",[129,370,371],{"class":135},"() ",[129,373,374],{"class":138},"{\n",[129,376,378,381],{"class":131,"line":377},7,[129,379,380],{"class":325},"    return",[129,382,332],{"class":138},[129,384,386,389,392],{"class":131,"line":385},8,[129,387,388],{"class":138},"      exampleMsg: ",[129,390,391],{"class":340},"'Hello emit!'",[129,393,344],{"class":138},[129,395,397],{"class":131,"line":396},9,[129,398,399],{"class":138},"    }\n",[129,401,403,405],{"class":131,"line":402},10,[129,404,359],{"class":138},[129,406,344],{"class":135},[129,408,410,413],{"class":131,"line":409},11,[129,411,412],{"class":135},"}",[129,414,415],{"class":138},";\n",[17,417,418],{},[44,419],{"alt":46,"src":420},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fz6eWY5Q.png",[17,422,423,424,427,428,430],{},"Next, add a lifecycle hook (",[21,425,426],{},"created","). The ",[21,429,306],{}," syntax is:",[120,432,434],{"className":122,"code":433,"language":124,"meta":125,"style":125},"this.$emit('custom event name', dataToSend);\n",[21,435,436],{"__ignoreMap":125},[129,437,438,442,444,446,449,452],{"class":131,"line":132},[129,439,441],{"class":440},"sCcAr","this",[129,443,40],{"class":138},[129,445,306],{"class":367},[129,447,448],{"class":138},"(",[129,450,451],{"class":340},"'custom event name'",[129,453,454],{"class":138},", dataToSend);\n",[17,456,457],{},[44,458],{"alt":46,"src":459},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fwmkwazz.png",[17,461,462,463,465],{},"The outbound emit is ready. Now over on the receiving side. Earlier we saw ",[21,464,23],{}," being passed in like this:",[17,467,468],{},[44,469],{"alt":46,"src":470},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FEpizSKS.png",[17,472,473,474,477,478,481,482,485],{},"On the receiving side you write your custom event name on the component along with the handler. One thing to watch — you ",[87,475,476],{},"can't use the shorthand"," (",[21,479,480],{},"@",") here. You have to write the full ",[21,483,484],{},"v-on",". So the correct form is:",[120,487,489],{"className":122,"code":488,"language":124,"meta":125,"style":125},"v-on:example='xxx'\n",[21,490,491],{"__ignoreMap":125},[129,492,493,496,499,502,505,508],{"class":131,"line":132},[129,494,495],{"class":138},"v",[129,497,498],{"class":325},"-",[129,500,501],{"class":135},"on",[129,503,504],{"class":138},":example",[129,506,507],{"class":325},"=",[129,509,510],{"class":340},"'xxx'\n",[17,512,513,514,517],{},"You also need a method on the receiver to handle the value, so adjust the ",[21,515,516],{},"Home"," data accordingly:",[17,519,520],{},[44,521],{"alt":46,"src":522},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FimcJLbE.png",[17,524,525],{},"Then wire up the handler:",[120,527,529],{"className":122,"code":528,"language":124,"meta":125,"style":125},"v-on:example='exampleEmit'\n",[21,530,531],{"__ignoreMap":125},[129,532,533,535,537,539,541,543],{"class":131,"line":132},[129,534,495],{"class":138},[129,536,498],{"class":325},[129,538,501],{"class":135},[129,540,504],{"class":138},[129,542,507],{"class":325},[129,544,545],{"class":340},"'exampleEmit'\n",[17,547,548],{},"Open the browser and you'll see the data passing from inside the component back out.",[17,550,551],{},[44,552],{"alt":46,"src":553},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FDcubqwZ.png",[17,555,556],{},"Visualized:",[17,558,559],{},[44,560],{"alt":46,"src":561},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FpgLx3k8.png",[12,563,565],{"id":564},"wrap-up","Wrap-up",[17,567,568,569,24,571,573],{},"People often mix up ",[21,570,23],{},[21,572,27],{},", so here's a single image that captures the whole flow. Once you understand the direction of the data, building things gets a lot easier.",[17,575,576],{},[44,577],{"alt":46,"src":578},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F7tCaRHy.png",[580,581,582],"style",{},"html pre.shiki code .s_sBn, html code.shiki .s_sBn{--shiki-default:#FFB757}html pre.shiki code .sMAXC, html code.shiki .sMAXC{--shiki-default:#F0F3F6}html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default